Veteran actor, Romanus Amuta, popularly known as ‘Natty’ in the foremost soap, ‘New Masquerade’ is dead. The New Masquerade was one of the most popular soaps of the 1980s. Amuta died on Feb. 9, 2022 at the age of 79 after a protracted sickness. The first son of the deceased, Dr Chukwuma Amuta confirmed the death of the veteran Nollywood actor in a telephone interview with the News Agency of Nigeria in Enugu. Amuta described the actor as a caring father who did his best to raise his children. “Yes! My father died this morning in Lagos after a protracted illness,” he said.       Veteran comedic actor, Romanus Uchenna Amuta aka ‘Natty’ who starred in the 1980s cinematic classic ‘New Masquerade’ has passed on. He reportedly died yesterday morning. The actor was partially paralysed, as a result of stroke. Before his death, Natty was one of the few surviving cast of the once celebrated… In "Entertainment" I am very much alive” Mr. Romanus Amuta popularly known as natty from the evergreen sitcom of the 80’s New masquerade cries out after a blogger Julia Blaise began to circulate news of his death. While speaking with Nollywood Television live in Enugu, the comic actor praised the president of… In "Style" By Rotimi Ijikanmi Abuja -   The Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, has expressed his condolences to the friends and family of veteran Kannywood actor, Kasimu Yero who died on Sunday in Kaduna. In a statement issued in Lagos on Monday, the Minister described the late Yero… In "Top Stories"